pulltitle: Fix startup to not affect Firefox performance.
pullsbody:
See the discussion in [bug 1415467](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1415467). This fixes startup when built as part of Firefox, it also changes the WebExtension startup so that we don't impact Firefox's startup performance.

We still need to handle performance of the background script, but this is a step in the right direction.
pull_repo_desc: FF System Add-on for Follow-on search telemetry
pull_commit_message: Fix starting up the WebExtension when built as part of Firefox, and change startup to not affect Firefox performance.

pulltitle: Handle Yahoo single URL searches
pullsbody:
So as of late, Yahoo has switched us so that when you do searches in other countries via yahoo.com, it redirects to the correct local Yahoo.

The side effect of this is that uk.yahoo.com (and any other country domain) is sometimes used with the old codes and sometimes used with the new codes. The codes was not designed to handle that.

I've put together a quick fix to handle this.
pull_repo_desc: FF System Add-on for Follow-on search telemetry
pull_commit_message: Handle Yahoo single URL searches

pulltitle: Bug 1404126 - Don't access the content object in the global scope to avoid triggering about:blank initialisation when it isn't needed.
pullsbody: Reported in [bug 1404126](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1404126), we're accessing the `content` object in the global scope. This can cause about:blank initialisation when a new tab is created and hence affects perf - so we should avoid it.
pull_repo_desc: FF System Add-on for Follow-on search telemetry
pull_commit_message: Bug 1404126 - Don't access the content object in the global scope to avoid triggering about:blank initialisation when it isn't needed.

pulltitle: Initialisation doesn't work during install() and isn't needed until startup
pullsbody:
According to https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/Add-ons/Bootstrapped_extensions#startup, startup gets called at installation and at other times.

Hence we don't need to do our initialisation on install - doing so causes errors that then stop the add-on starting up correctly.

This fixes that.
pull_repo_desc: FF System Add-on for Follow-on search telemetry
pull_commit_message: Initialisation doesn't work during install() and isn't needed until startup.

pulltitle: Google removed instant search so we need to detect followon differently
pullsbody:
So Google removed instant search which means follow on searches aren't indicated by hash (#) and the old search.

Now they pass a parameter called "oq"

So this has broken followon search tracking for a while.

pulltitle: Rewrite of framescript to primarily a progress listener
pullsbody:
Per @Mossop review comments, I've rewritten the framescript to mostly use progress listener (since we're dealing with URLs 99% of the time).

I had to keep the page load listener only to handle bing because we need cookies.

I looked into grabbing cookies in the progress listener, but onLocationChange seems to be too early for anything to have happend.
pull_repo_desc: FF System Add-on for Follow-on search telemetry
pull_commit_message: Rewrite of framescript to primarily a progress listener
